osu_versions.name: 1.6.1-osu-hidden
osu_versions.notes:
## What's new in firmware 1.6.1? 


Firmware version 1.6.1 brings several user experience improvements and additional cryptographic support. Please find more information about this update in our [blog post](https://www.ledger.com/ledger-nano-s-firmware-version-161-now-available).


**Before you update**

- In some rare cases, your device may be reset during the update. You will then have to restore it from your recovery phrase.

**Better user experience**

- Smooth update : no need to disconnect and reconnect the USB cable during firmware updates. Bootloader mode is now automatically launched to update the MCU firmware.
- Significantly reduced the delay when (un)installing multiple apps in the Manager.

**Other changes**

- Added cryptographic support for the BLS12-381 curve.
- Fixed functionality to switch between library contexts.

osu_versions.name: 1.6.1-osu
osu_versions.notes:
## What's new in firmware 1.6.1? 


- **Firmware version 1.6.0** brought security and cryptographic enhancements, many user experience improvements, increased app storage capacity, and bug fixes to the firmware version 1.5.5. Please find more information about the firmware version 1.6.0 in our [blog post](https://www.ledger.com/new-firmware-update-for-ledger-nano-s/). 

- **Firmware version 1.6.1** brings several user experience improvements and additional cryptographic support. Please find more information about this update in our [blog post](https://www.ledger.com/ledger-nano-s-firmware-version-161-now-available).


**Before you update**

- **Linux users** must add new udev rules **before the update**. [Learn more](https://support.ledger.com/hc/en-us/articles/360019301813-Fix-USB-issues)
- In some rare cases, your device may be reset during the update. You will then have to restore it from your recovery phrase.

**Better user experience**

- Significantly reduced the delay when (un)installing multiple apps in the Manager.

**Other changes**

- Added cryptographic support for the BLS12-381 curve.
- Fixed functionality to switch between library contexts.
